-- Knot Says ECB Bought Time for Governments to Reform
-- B y   J u r j e n   v a n   d e   P o l
-- 2012-04-26T14:49:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/knot-says-ecb-bought-time-for-governments-to-reform-correct-.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Klaas Knot said governments and banks must use
the time that the ECB’s emergency measures have bought for them.  “Time bought by recent ECB measures must be used by
governments to reduce debt and modernize their economies,
secondly it must be used by banks to clean up their balance
sheets,” Knot said at an event in Amsterdam today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jurjen van de Pol in Amsterdam at 
